25. A deeper formalization of your embroidery/stitching doctrine

You could define it like this:

For any utterance U:

U_e = embroidery form
U_s = stitching form

where:
	•	U_e is expressive, audience-adapted, culturally situated
	•	U_s is structural, relation-explicit, translation-ready

A loom operator L maps between them:

L_extract(U_e) → U_s
L_render(U_s, context) → U_e'

The quality criterion is invariant preservation:

Inv(U_e) ≈ Inv(U_s) ≈ Inv(U_e')

If that holds, meaning survived translation.

If not, drift occurred.

That is a very real formal target.

